ervations as well as the ambiguities and limitation inherent to the Hanle\neffect when only the hydrogen Lyman-$\\alpha$ is used. We conclude that\nspectropolarimetric observations with CLASP can indeed be a suitable diagnostic\ntool for probing the magnetism of the transition region, especially when\ncomplemented with information on the magnetic field azimuth that can be\nobtained from other instruments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 3 Apr 2014 07:33:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
